The '''Giryulan Findings''' were an infamous event that took place at some point by the time of the [[Imperial Era/Legends|reign]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and shared their name with<ref name="AIR">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref> the [[Giryulan system/Legends|Giryulan system]] of [[Wild Space/Legends|Wild Space]].<ref name="Atlas Online">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> At one point by [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'' represents a collection of [[in-universe]] reports from "one [[Standard year/Legends|year]] before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]," which corresponds to [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> an ambitious [[Imperial officer/Legends|officer]] of the [[Imperial Survey Corps/Legends|Imperial Survey Corps]] framed the Corps' loyal [[Scout/Legends|scout]] [[Stren Grier]]&mdash;who they were a [[Commanding officer/Legends|commanding officer]] of&mdash;of falsifying several reports regarding the Giryulan Findings. As a result, Grier was forced to flee [[Imperial Space|Imperial-controlled space]] and subsequently became a staffmember of the [[Galactic Outdoor Survival School/Legends|Galactic Outdoor Survival School]].<ref name="AIR" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Giryulan Findings were mentioned in ''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]'', a [[1995]] sourcebook for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="AIR" />

